# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Midcenturist CMS Environment Configuration
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values
# Do NOT commit .env.local to version control

# API Configuration
# The Flask API base URL. Use Render production URL for deployed instances.
# Local development: http://localhost:5000
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://midcenturist-api.onrender.com

# NextAuth Configuration
# IMPORTANT: Generate a long random string for security
# Run: openssl rand -base64 32
NEXTAUTH_SECRET=your-long-random-secret-here-change-this-in-production

# The CMS URL — used by NextAuth for callback URLs in auth flow
# Local development: http://localhost:3001
NEXTAUTH_URL=http://localhost:3001

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# CREDENTIALS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# The CMS authenticates against a Flask API endpoint at POST /api/admin/login
# Credentials are validated on the Flask API, not stored in this CMS.
# These environment variables are NOT used for authentication here.
# Instead, contact the API admin to verify credentials are set on Render.

# Admin Email (for reference — validated against Flask ADMIN_EMAIL)
ADMIN_EMAIL=hello@midcenturist.co.za

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# 1. LOCAL DEVELOPMENT
#    cp .env.local.example .env.local
#    Edit .env.local with your values
#    npm run dev     # Starts CMS on http://localhost:3001

# 2. VERIFY FLASK API IS WORKING
#    curl https://midcenturist-api.onrender.com/api/health
#    Should return 200 OK

# 3. TEST AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINT
#    curl -X POST https://midcenturist-api.onrender.com/api/admin/login \
#      -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
#      -d '{"email":"hello@midcenturist.co.za","password":"your-admin-password"}'
#
#    Expected response: { "token": "eyJ0eXAiOiJKV1QiLCJhbGc...", "expires_in": 86400 }
#
#    If you see "Invalid credentials" or 401, check:
#    - Email matches ADMIN_EMAIL on Flask API (case-insensitive)
#    - Password matches the one used to generate ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH on Flask
#    - Both environment variables are set on Render deployment

# 4. FIRST LOGIN TO CMS
#    • Go to http://localhost:3001/login
#    • Enter email and password
#    • Click "Sign In"
#    • You should be redirected to http://localhost:3001/dashboard

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# TROUBLESHOOTING
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# "Invalid email or password" at login
# → Test Flask API directly with curl (see TEST AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINT above)
# → Verify Flask API is deployed and accessible

# Middleware redirecting to /login on protected routes
# → Check NEXTAUTH_SECRET is set and consistent across restarts
# → Check NEXTAUTH_URL matches your deployment URL

# 401 errors from API calls
# → Verify the Flask JWT token is being passed with Bearer auth
# → Check token expiry (24 hours default)
# → Test with: curl -H "Authorization: Bearer <token>" \
#   https://midcenturist-api.onrender.com/api/admin/products

# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# FLASK API SETUP (for reference)
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# The Flask API at https://midcenturist-api.onrender.com must have:
#
# 1. Environment variables set on Render:
#    ADMIN_EMAIL=hello@midcenturist.co.za
#    ADMIN_PASSWORD_HASH=<bcrypt hash of password>
#
# 2. POST /api/admin/login endpoint implemented (see implementation_cms.md)
#
# 3. Bearer token validation on all /api/admin/* endpoints
#
# Contact the API admin or check the Flask repo for setup details.

